.TH "scmi_xfer_get" 9 "scmi_xfer_get" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scmi_xfer_get \- Allocate one message
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct scmi_xfer *" scmi_xfer_get
.BI "(const struct scmi_handle *handle "  ","
.BI "struct scmi_xfers_info *minfo "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "handle" 12
Pointer to SCMI entity handle
.IP "minfo" 12
Pointer to Tx/Rx Message management info based on channel type
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Helper function which is used by various message functions that are
exposed to clients of this driver for allocating a message traffic event.

This function can sleep depending on pending requests already in the system
for the SCMI entity. Further, this also holds a spinlock to maintain
integrity of internal data structures.
.SH "RETURN"
0 if all went fine, else corresponding error.
